-- Puerto Rico electric utility to pay ABR plus 4 pct on credit lines -filing
-- By Hilary Russ and Ed Krudy
-- Thu Aug 14, 2014 07:39PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Aug 14 (Reuters) - Puerto Rico's electric power authority, known as PREPA, will pay an interest rate of alternate base rate (ABR) plus 4 percent under credit agreements with Scotiabank <BNS.TO> and Citibank <C.N>, the utility said in a filing on Thursday.

